  "body": "I have 3 **Amazon Ec2 instances** (each with a Geth node running on them) and I'm running over them my Private **Geth** Ethereum (PoA) blokchain and I wanted to ask if is possible to specify the IPs of all 3 of my amazon AWS machines when I define the\r\n\r\n```\r\nnetworks:{\r\n   geth:{\r\n      host: ip-aws-machine,\r\n      port: 8546,            \r\n      network_id: \"netID\",       \r\n      from: \"address\",  \r\n   }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nin the `truffle_config.js`.\r\n\r\nFor example, if the machine with the ip that I entered in `truffle_config.js` shuts down, my network will be unusable.\r\nIs there a way to handle this in case a machine stops working to outsource work to another IP?",
